| X9 | `certification` + `rewards` → `reputation` | 5 | `AgentReputation` | Re-exported `AgentReputation` from `reputation/services/reputation_service.py` (service layer = public API). Added `get_reputation_by_agent(agent_id)` query method. 5 consumers updated to import from service module instead of domain module. |

**Result: zero cross-context domain-model imports remain.** The only remaining imports are:
- **Intra-context** (each context imports from its own `domain/`) — correct

### Legacy flat-domain imports — eliminated ✅

The 12 legacy flat-domain imports (from `app/domain/*.py`) were migrated to their owning bounded contexts in the same release. The `bounty.py` file was split across 3 contexts (bounty, staking, ecosystem) since it contained models for all three domains.

| # | Model file | Migrated to | Files updated | Notes |
|---|-----------|-------------|---------------|-------|
| L1 | `domain/bounty.py` | `contexts/bounty/domain/bounty.py` | 2 (bounty router, bounty_service) | Bounty-specific models (Bounty, BountySubmission, BountyIntegration, BountyStats, enums) |
| L2 | `domain/bounty.py` (staking models) | `contexts/staking/domain/staking.py` | 2 (staking router, staking_service) | Staking-specific models split from bounty.py (AgentStake, AgentMetrics, StakingPool, StakeStatus, PerformanceTier) |
| L3 | `domain/bounty.py` (ecosystem metrics) | `contexts/ecosystem/domain/ecosystem.py` | 1 (ecosystem_service) | EcosystemMetrics split from bounty.py |
| L4 | `domain/community.py` | `contexts/community/domain/community.py` | 2 (community router, community_service) | All community models |
| L5 | `domain/developer_platform.py` | `contexts/developer_platform/domain/developer_platform.py` | 3 (router, service, schema) | All developer_platform models |
| L6 | `domain/governance.py` | `contexts/governance/domain/governance.py` | 3 (2 routers, governance_service) | All governance models |
| L7 | `domain/dao_governance.py` | `contexts/governance/domain/dao_governance.py` | 2 (dao_governance_service, schema) | All DAO governance models |
| L8 | `domain/pricing_models.py` | `contexts/trading/domain/pricing_models.py` | 1 (dynamic_pricing) | All pricing models |
| L9 | `domain/wallet.py` | `contexts/wallet/domain/wallet.py` | 3 (2 wallet services, schema) | All wallet models |

**Result: zero legacy flat-domain imports from `contexts/` remain.** All 7 model files deleted from `app/domain/`. 10 flat domain files remain (`agent_portfolio.py`, `atomic_swap.py`, etc.) but these are only imported from `services/`, `schemas/`, `routers/`, `reputation/`, and `settlement/` — not from `contexts/`, so they're outside the bounded-context migration scope.

